  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to compare the two imaging modalities perfusion weighted MR-imaging
      and FET-PET in their ability to provide an accurate histological evaluation of low grade
      glioma and to reveal focal abnormalities within a homogeneously appearing tumor.
      Additionally, therapeutic effects should be assessed during a time period of two years.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
